issue.body:
### URL(s) with the issue

https://docs.voxel51.com/user_guide/dataset_zoo/datasets.html#dataset-zoo-voc-2012

### Description of proposal (what needs changing)

Hi,

according to the documentation, VOC2012 and VOC2007 "test" splits are available in the tf backend. Unfortunately Iam not able to download the test split for the two datasets:

ValueError: Invalid split 'test'; supported values are ('train', 'validation')

As far as I  have understood, the base class automatically chooses the backend for which the split exists?

Thanks in advance,

best regards,

M

### Willingness to contribute

The FiftyOne Community encourages documentation contributions. Would you or another member of your organization be willing to contribute a fix for this documentation issue to the FiftyOne codebase?

-   [ ] Yes. I would be willing to contribute a documentation fix with guidance from the FiftyOne community
-   [ x] No. I cannot contribute a documentation fix at this time

comment.body:
@MLRadfys thanks for your contribution to making FiftyOne better! I believe this is happening because you have both torch and tensorflow installed in your environment. By default, FiftyOne chooses torch as the ML backend.

I have confirmed that if you set `default_ml_backend` config to `"tensorflow"` then the test split will download properly!
I agree the documentation around how to resolve this could be better so I'll try to add something.

Example:
```
import fiftyone as fo
fo.config.default_ml_backend="tensorflow"
fo.zoo.load_zoo_dataset("voc-2012", split="test")
```

Here is the relevant snippet from the [configuration table](https://docs.voxel51.com/user_guide/config.html).

default_ml_backend | FIFTYONE_DEFAULT_ML_BACKEND | torch | The default ML backend to use when performing operations such as downloading datasets from the FiftyOne Dataset Zoo that support multiple ML backends. Supported values are torch and tensorflow. By default, torch is used if PyTorch is installed in your Python environment, and tensorflow is used if TensorFlow is installed. If no supported backend is detected, this defaults to None, and any operation that requires an installed ML backend will raise an informative error message if invoked in this state.
-- | -- | -- | --

issue.title: [FR] Add support for URL-based samples

labels.name: needs design
labels.description: Issues related to features that need more design

labels.name: server
labels.description: Issues related to server features or changes

issue.body:
### Proposal Summary

Proposing URLs are supported as a  sample's `filepath`. Or, perhaps a mutually exclusive reserved field, `url`, is added. Furthermore, it would be ideal if datasets could support a mixture of `filepath` and `url` samples.

### Motivation

Adding support for URL-backed samples, as opposed disk-backed samples, would increase the flexibility and agility of creating FiftyOne datasets.

### What areas of FiftyOne does this feature affect?

-   [x] App: FiftyOne application
-   [x] Core: Core `fiftyone` Python library
-   [x] Server: FiftyOne server

comment.body: @tadejsv this is currently a Teams feature. In OSS you can use [cloud storage](https://docs.voxel51.com/faq/index.html#can-i-access-data-stored-in-the-cloud) by mounting the cloud bucket as a filesystem. I'm not sure of a workaround for URL paths though.
